{{Use Australian English|date=May 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date= May 2015}} {{Infobox Australian place | type = protected | name = Blackwood Forest Recreation Park | state = sa | iucn_category = iii | image = | caption = | image_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|35|1|42.6|S|138|37|42.96|E|display=inline,title}} | force_national_map = | relief = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | map_alt = | nearest_town_or_city = Adelaide city centre | area = {{convert|21|ha|abbr=off}} | area_footnotes =<ref name=ReserveList>{{cite web|title=Protected Areas Information System - reserve list (as of 25 November 2014)|url=http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/b88e6e26-4bd9-4c68-8fff-9e800114eb69/park-management-protected-areas-gen.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment Water and Natural Resources|accessdate=8 January 2015|pages=}}</ref> | established = {{start date|2001|11|01|df=y}} | established_footnotes =<ref name=ReserveList/> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_footnotes = <ref name=MP/> | managing_authorities = [[Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources (South Australia)|Department of Environment, Water and Natural Resources]] | url = }} '''Blackwood Forest Recreation Park''' is a [[protected area]] located about {{convert|12|km|abbr=off}} south of the [[Adelaide city centre]] in the suburb of [[Hawthorndene, South Australia|Hawthorndene]]. The recreation park was proclaimed under the ''[[National Parks and Wildlife Act 1972]]'' in 2001 to retain land purchased in 1908 by the [[Government of South Australia]] for use as open space for recreational purposes. The recreation park is classified as an [[International Union for Conservation of Nature|IUCN]] [[IUCN protected area categories#Category III — Natural Monument or Feature|Category III protected area]].<ref name=MP>{{cite web|title= Blackwood Forest Recreation Park Management Plan |url= http://www.environment.sa.gov.au/files/sharedassets/public/park_management/parks_pdfs_blackwood_forest_mp.pdf|publisher=Department of Environment and Heritage|date=2005|accessdate=8 May 2015|pages=i & ii}}</ref><ref name=CAPAD2014SASum>{{cite web|title= Terrestrial Protected Areas of South Australia (see 'DETAIL' tab)|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/system/files/pages/d00ca066-1c8c-412a-9e16-2a37647454a7/files/capad2014sa.xlsx|work=CAPAD 2012|publisher=Australian Government - Department of the Environment|accessdate=13 March 2015|date=2014}}</ref>
