ral Italy)|url=http://www.annalsofgeophysics.eu/index.php/annals/article/view/6645|first=A.|last=Tertulliani|first2=V.|last2=Castelli|first3=A.|last3=Rossi|first4=M.|last4=Vecchi|year=2014|journal=Annals of Geophysics|publisher=[[National Institute of Geophysics and Volcanology|Istituto Nazionale Geofisica e Vulcanologia]]|volume=57|number=6|pages=1, 7, 8|doi=10.4401/ag-6645}}</ref> |- | [[1936 Cansiglio earthquake|1936-10-18]] || [[Cansiglio]] || 5.9 M<sub>L</sub> || IX || 19 || || || |- | [[1930 Senigallia earthquake|1930-10-30]] || [[Senigallia]], [[Marche]] || 5.9 || || 18 || || || |- | [[1930 Irpinia earthquake|1930-07-23]] || [[Irpinia]] || 6.6 M<sub>s</sub> || X || 1,404 || 4,624–7,000 || || |- | [[1920 Garfagnana earthquake|1920-09-07]] || [[Garfagnana]] || 6.4 || || 171 || || || <ref name=usgs/> |- | 1917-04-26 || Northern [[Umbria]] || 5.8 || || 20 || || || |- | [[1915 Avezzano earthquake|1915-01-13]] || [[Province of L'Aquila|L'Aquila]] || | 6.7 M<sub>w</sub> || XI || 29,978–32,610 || || Extreme damage || |- | 1914-05-08 || [[Sicily]] || 4.9 M<sub>s</sub> || X || 120 || || Severe damage || {{harvnb|NGDC}} |- | [[1908 Messina earthquake|1908-12-28]] || [[Strait of Messina]] || 7.1 M<sub>w</sub> || XI || 75,000–200,000 || || Extreme damage / tsunami || |- | [[1907 Calabria earthquake|1907-10-23]] || [[Calabria]] || 5.9 M<sub>s</sub> || VIII–X || 158–167 || || Moderate damage || {{harvnb|NGDC}} |- | [[1905 Calabria earthquake|1905-09-08]] || [[Calabria]] || 7.2 M<sub>w</sub> || XI || 557–2,500 || || Tsunami || |- | 1901-10-30 || [[Salò]] || 5.5 M<sub>w</sub> || VII–VIII|| || || Collapsed buildings || <ref>{{citation|title=The revision of the 30 October 1901 earthquake west of Lake Garda (northern Italy)|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/235224607_The_revision_of_the_30_October_1901_earthquake_west_of_Lake_Garda_northern_Italy|first=V.|last=Pessina|first2=A.|last2=Tertulliani|first3=C.|last3=Romano|first4=G.|last4=Scardia|year=2013|journal=Bolletti